data.title: Declaration of Intention for Giovanni Stracuzzi
data.text:
Description

Date Created1917

Extent1 pages

DescriptionDeclaration of Intention to become a citizen of the United States, as filled out and signed by Giovanni Stracuzzi. Applicant lists himself as a 22 year old shoemaker residing in Hammonton, New Jersey, born in Messina, Italy on 16 October 1894, who sailed on the US bound vessel Taormina. Declaration submitted and sworn June 7, 1917.

Genreforms (documents), government records, immigration records, naturalization records, legal documents, official documents

LanguageEnglish

CollectionAtlantic County Immigration Records
